@node DECSRIPTION "What is BBInstall?"

	What is BBInstall?
	------------------
	
	Not so long ago, I got a disk from some PD company that had
	a whole lot of programming tools on it.  One of these was a 
	description of how the Amiga translates a Boot Block, what
	it does and what it expects it to return.  I was impressed.
	
	The only problem was that the utilitiy included was, in a word,
	hopeless.  It was supposed to convert an executable code into
	a bootblock but if didn't work, assuming a fixed size for the
	header info.  so I wrote a program to replace it.
	
	BBInstall can install or save trackdisk.device Boot Blocks.
	It can load executable code or an object file, provided it
	has only one code hunk.  (Actually, it can have as many code
	hunks as you like.  BBInstall will only install the first one).
	It can also load raw data, ans can save either as an executable
	or as data.  It recalculates the checksum on before installing
	the bootblock.
	
